docs.lead_paragraph: LEAD: Cerebral palsy was long believed to result mainly from interference with the baby's oxygen supply during labor and delivery. But researchers are now finding that this assumption is rarely correct.

docs.lead_paragraph: LEAD: MOST Americans had likely never heard of the diet supplement L-tryptophan until last month. Since Nov. 11, when the Food and Drug Administration issued an alert to the public to stop taking L-tryptophan supplements, it has been in the news almost every week. On Dec. 5, the agency recalled the product from stores and detained all imports of the supplement.
